        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 4:24PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 423 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Mountain Lake, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail and wind gusts up to 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Loose objects may be knocked over due to gusty winds.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Alleghany...
White Sulphur Springs...
New Castle...
Newport...
Paint Bank...
and Sinking Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
